populo plebique] this phrase is a survival from a time when the plebs were a mass of dependent aliens outside the populus = patricii, the latter alone being burgesses and engrossing all political power. We find it elsewhere, as in the title of adfizm x 35, 11 in Verrem V §36 and in the latter of the carmina splarciana quoted in Liv XXV 12.
